# Marketing content sync

## Source repos (sibling to ZukiApps-WEB)

`/Users/zukman/GIT/{AppName}/` — scan:

- `marketing/shared/guides/faq.md`, `user-manual.md`, `tips-and-tricks.md`
- `marketing/shared/website/landing-page.md`, `copy/locales.json`
- `marketing/android/screenshots/`, `marketing/shared/branding/app-icon-512.png`
- `docs/APP_STORE_LISTING_*.md`, `GOOGLE_PLAY_LISTING_*.md`

## Patch workflow

1. English only first: `messages/en.json` namespace (`hero`, `features`, `faq.items`, …)
2. Optional script: `scripts/patch-{slug}-content.py`
3. Assets: `public/images/{slug}/`, icon at `public/images/{slug}-icon.png`
4. Page: mirror `hush-gallery` or `whistle-camera` section order
5. Update `public/llms.txt` + `public/{slug}/faq.md`

## Copy rules

- Lead with user benefit, not tech stack (unless dev-focused app like Bit Scope)
- FAQ answers: concrete steps, real URLs (`https://zukiapps.com/...`)
- No placeholder screenshots (black/empty viewer frames)
- Version in `status.versionValue` from app marketing version when known

| ZuList | `Marketing/` | `/zulist` | `zulist` |
| BitScope | `Marketing/` | `/bit-scope` | `bitScope` |
